Call. This species is crepuscular and calls from within leaf litter in primary forest at dawn and dusk. Its call consists of a continuous series of high-pitched notes with a dominant frequency of ~ 8400–9400 Hz. Individual notes range in duration from 2– 14 ms and are produced at a rate of 1.5 notes/s (
Fig. 2
;
Table 3
). The overall acoustic impression is that of a stridulating insect. Individuals generally call from one to three minutes and then rest briefly before resuming. In a 5.5 minute recorded sequence, one individual ( NS 2 ,
Table 3
) produced a total of 355 calls in four groups, with the interval between groups ranging from
3.3 to 40.8 s
.

